messages.title: Council Tax Increase
messages.content: In six years Council Tax has risen by 27% a time of unprecedented low general inflation. Enough really is enough. At the same time as yet another above inflation rise charges for Council services will rise twice next financial year in April and October.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Criticizes the 27% Council Tax increase over six years, emphasizing that it's a significant rise during a time of low general inflation. Opposes further above-inflation charges for Council services.

housing.content: Criticizes the state of the Tucker Field alongside the new development on the Old School site, suggesting that it stands neglected and unused as a consequence of the Cabinets' inaction.
